title: $:/plugins/rimir/kind/settings
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

\whitespace trim
\import $:/plugins/rimir/kind/engine

!! Active namespace

<div style="font-size:0.9em;opacity:0.75;margin-bottom:6px;">
Restricts the //creator//, //overview//, and //validator// to a single namespace. Choose <em>(all)</em> to see every type regardless of namespace.
</div>

<div class="kind-ns-row">
Namespace:
<$select tiddler="$:/config/rimir/kind/active-namespace">
<option value="">(all)</option>
<$list filter="[function[kind.namespaces-all]]" variable="ns">
<option value=<<ns>>><<ns>></option>
</$list>
</$select>
</div>

!! Default type prefix

<div style="font-size:0.9em;opacity:0.75;margin-bottom:6px;">
When you enter a short name in the //type-builder// (e.g. <code>task</code>), this prefix is prepended to form the full tiddler title. A title starting with <code>$:/</code> is used as-is.
</div>

<div class="kind-ns-row">
<strong>Prefix:</strong>
<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/rimir/kind/type-prefix" field="text" tag="input" class="kind-input" default="$:/config/rimir/kind/types/"/>
</div>

!! Stream-view truncation

<div style="font-size:0.9em;opacity:0.75;margin-bottom:6px;">
Maximum characters per field value shown in the stream-river field bar. Longer values are truncated with an ellipsis. Click a field to pop up the full editor.
</div>

<div class="kind-ns-row">
Max length:
<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/rimir/kind/streambar-max-length" field="text" tag="input" type="number" class="kind-input" default="20" style="width:6em;"/>
</div>

!! Type selector in the story river

<div style="font-size:0.9em;opacity:0.75;margin-bottom:6px;">
Tiddlers that already have a kind type show the type icon in the field bar as a <strong>picker</strong> — click it to change or remove the type. Enable the option below to also show a compact <code>＋ type</code> picker under the title of tiddlers that have //no// kind type yet, so you can assign one. The qualifying filter controls which untyped tiddlers get that picker. Only <em>top-level</em> types in the active namespace are offered.
</div>

<div class="kind-ns-row">
<$checkbox tiddler="$:/config/rimir/kind/type-selector-enable" field="text" checked="yes" unchecked="no" default="yes"/> Show <code>＋ type</code> on untyped tiddlers
</div>

<div class="kind-ns-row">
<strong>Qualifying filter:</strong>
<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/rimir/kind/type-selector-filter" field="text" tag="input" class="kind-input" default="[all[current]!is[system]!has[draft.of]]" style="width:24em;"/>
</div>
